WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.680
Charlotte Wells
has been arrested.

00:02.680 --> 00:04.160
I did not kill Sir George

00:04.160 --> 00:05.760
and nor did Daniel Marney.

00:05.760 --> 00:06.920
Where is Mr. North?

00:06.920 --> 00:08.160
I don't know where he is.

00:08.160 --> 00:10.160
If he's left you
then good on him!

00:10.160 --> 00:11.760
I will scream what
I know from the rooftops

00:11.760 --> 00:13.080
if you force me.

00:13.080 --> 00:14.480
It's all I have, take it.

00:14.480 --> 00:16.760
The house and the girl
are compromised.

00:16.760 --> 00:18.840
I will need to replace both.

00:18.840 --> 00:20.680
I want a seat at the table,

00:20.680 --> 00:22.200
as you promised me.

00:22.200 --> 00:23.800
Tread carefully, John.

00:23.800 --> 00:25.200
♪

00:25.200 --> 00:26.480
He was already dead as flint

00:26.480 --> 00:28.280
when he left the Wells'
brothel last night.

00:28.280 --> 00:29.600
I won't see Charlotte
put to death

00:29.600 --> 00:30.800
for something I did.

00:30.800 --> 00:32.200
Get out!

00:32.200 --> 01:06.160
♪

01:06.160 --> 01:08.760
She's a beauty.

01:08.760 --> 01:10.400
Just like her ma.

01:10.400 --> 01:11.760
♪

01:11.760 --> 01:14.680
She has a big smell.

01:14.680 --> 01:16.240
Like the sea.

01:16.240 --> 01:18.760
♪

01:18.760 --> 01:20.520
I never want to let her go.

01:20.520 --> 01:24.320
♪

01:24.320 --> 01:26.880
You know how it has to be.

01:26.880 --> 01:28.480
We're not a nursery.

01:28.480 --> 01:32.680
♪

01:34.960 --> 01:37.160
I felt since I was
a boy there was a noose

01:37.160 --> 01:40.240
waiting somewhere
with my name on it.

01:40.240 --> 01:42.040
I've avoided it so far.

01:44.600 --> 01:46.320
And then I met you.

01:50.880 --> 01:52.400
Do you doubt me?

01:54.480 --> 01:57.400
Only one of us need kiss
the rope and you know it.

01:57.400 --> 01:59.040
You could condemn
my mother and my sister

01:59.040 --> 02:00.120
with a word.

02:00.120 --> 02:01.680
Why don't you?

02:01.680 --> 02:03.120
Because you'd despise me.

02:03.120 --> 02:05.880
You could free yourself.

02:05.880 --> 02:07.520
And who'd believe me?

02:09.080 --> 02:10.680
I'm a desperate man.

02:12.360 --> 02:16.080
♪

02:16.080 --> 02:18.800
(crowd chatter)

02:18.800 --> 02:35.640
♪

02:39.720 --> 02:41.960
The Wells' house,
Greek Street.

02:51.560 --> 02:52.520
Lord Fallon.

02:55.520 --> 02:58.280
The Spartans will receive you.

02:58.280 --> 03:00.120
I am most gratified.

03:00.120 --> 03:01.400
You'll bring a handmaiden

03:01.400 --> 03:03.240
to demonstrate your fealty.

03:03.240 --> 03:06.400
In quality, exceptional.

03:08.120 --> 03:09.360
Intact.

03:11.400 --> 03:13.720
My lord, I need time.

03:13.720 --> 03:16.680
Such maidens are...

03:16.680 --> 03:18.720
not easily found.

03:20.640 --> 03:23.120
The procuress
I formerly used

03:23.120 --> 03:26.120
has proven...inadequate.

03:27.800 --> 03:29.520
I trust there is no danger.

03:29.520 --> 03:32.520
Let me assure you
of her silence.

03:37.120 --> 03:40.000
We meet tonight.

03:40.000 --> 03:41.680
A-hunting you must go.

03:47.440 --> 03:49.800
I must go to the courthouse,
the trial is tomorrow.

03:49.800 --> 03:52.520
I want you to go to Nancy's
until this trouble's passed.

03:52.520 --> 03:54.440
Nancy's turned against you.

03:54.440 --> 03:56.680
But never you.

03:56.680 --> 03:58.280
This come.

03:58.280 --> 04:01.000
I take one cull and if another
wants his prick sucked,

04:01.000 --> 04:02.680
see to him yourself.

04:09.720 --> 04:11.400
It's from Lord Fallon.

04:13.240 --> 04:15.120
His contract.

04:15.120 --> 04:16.560
Oh, I forgot.

04:16.560 --> 04:19.640
He offers 400
guineas on my head.

04:19.640 --> 04:21.400
I'll go with him...

04:21.400 --> 04:23.560
like I should have done.

04:23.560 --> 04:25.120
-No.
-If I'd done what you asked,

04:25.120 --> 04:26.840
we wouldn't be in this calamity.

04:26.840 --> 04:28.320
You will not go with him.

04:28.320 --> 04:30.440
He offers so much money.

04:30.440 --> 04:33.240
Well, I'd rather
be dead than take it.

04:33.240 --> 04:35.320
No.

04:35.320 --> 04:37.680
I will never force
a man on you again.

04:42.000 --> 04:43.080
Burn it.

04:45.560 --> 04:47.400
I gave him very
pressing evidence

04:47.400 --> 04:49.880
about the kidnap of
a young and helpless girl.

04:49.880 --> 04:51.200
I told him who
the culprit was,

04:51.200 --> 04:52.640
the bawd, Mrs. Quigley.

04:52.640 --> 04:55.760
Yet, Justice Cunliffe
has done nothing.

04:55.760 --> 04:57.200
I've known him for 25 years,

04:57.200 --> 04:58.880
he's meticulous.

04:58.880 --> 05:00.240
Perhaps your
evidence is faulty.

05:00.240 --> 05:02.240
No, sir, I was there.

05:07.080 --> 05:10.000
That room stank
of fear and murder.

05:10.000 --> 05:12.560
I was going to
die there, I know it.

05:12.560 --> 05:14.840
Did you shit yourself?

05:14.840 --> 05:16.000
No.

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
Quigley should be
butchered in her bed.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.120
Her exit must be public.

05:20.120 --> 05:23.560
I want to see her legs
cavort when she hangs.

05:23.560 --> 05:25.640
That means going
to the justice.

05:25.640 --> 05:28.200
Quigley's got his
pintle in her fist.

05:28.200 --> 05:31.560
Well, you're a little
powderkeg, Emily.

05:31.560 --> 05:33.200
You can bring them
both to their knees.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.560
Stab the bitch
through the eyeballs.

05:35.560 --> 05:36.880
(snorts)

05:40.560 --> 05:42.640
There is more than
one way to bleed a sow.

05:42.640 --> 05:54.640
♪

05:54.640 --> 05:56.320
You saw Sir George Howard

05:56.320 --> 05:59.440
carried out of
the Wells' house dead.

05:59.440 --> 06:01.440
I saw no such thing.

06:01.440 --> 06:03.680
Don't deny it.

06:03.680 --> 06:05.240
My molly boy saw it, too,

06:05.240 --> 06:06.560
and were he a credible witness

06:06.560 --> 06:08.520
I'd have him at
the courthouse now.

06:08.520 --> 06:10.680
Amelia would
never tell a lie.

06:10.680 --> 06:13.840
I thought Sir George drunk.

06:13.840 --> 06:15.440
Men leave the Wells' house

06:15.440 --> 06:17.320
in all manner of
inebriated states.

06:17.320 --> 06:19.880
He was dead!

06:19.880 --> 06:23.760
And your word
will carry a jury.

06:23.760 --> 06:27.680
That's a dreadful accusation.

06:27.680 --> 06:30.000
It could cost
Mrs. Wells her life.

06:30.000 --> 06:34.120
My girl won't speak
against her conscience.

06:34.120 --> 06:36.240
She is not capable.

06:36.240 --> 06:38.840
She is capable
and culpable

06:38.840 --> 06:41.880
of the most
grotesque deceit.

06:41.880 --> 06:44.000
She is virtue itself.

06:44.000 --> 06:46.240
Indeed.

06:46.240 --> 06:49.080
She is a paragon.

06:49.080 --> 06:52.760
Beloved by women...

06:52.760 --> 06:55.120
everywhere.

06:55.120 --> 06:56.640
♪

06:56.640 --> 06:59.400
I saw Sir George Howard

06:59.400 --> 07:03.640
carried out of
the Wells' house.

07:03.640 --> 07:08.400
I thought him drunk
and insensible.

07:08.400 --> 07:13.080
But then I heard his
body had been found and--

07:13.080 --> 07:16.120
Are you telling me
that he was already dead?

07:16.120 --> 07:17.560
♪

07:17.560 --> 07:19.200
Is that what you are saying?

07:19.200 --> 07:23.200
♪

07:23.200 --> 07:24.440
Yes.

07:24.440 --> 07:26.560
♪

07:26.560 --> 07:29.760
Thank you for
bringing this to me.

07:29.760 --> 07:32.880
Your virtue shines through.

07:32.880 --> 07:41.200
♪

07:41.200 --> 07:43.440
(crowd chatter)

07:49.440 --> 07:51.000
It's Harriet.

07:51.000 --> 07:52.880
Wait, Jacob!

07:52.880 --> 07:54.840
Harriet!

07:54.840 --> 07:56.760
(Harriet chuckles)

07:56.760 --> 07:58.000
Why are you here?

07:58.000 --> 08:00.640
Well, I had the
same question for you.

08:00.640 --> 08:04.320
I've come to see if I
can rescue my children.

08:04.320 --> 08:05.760
Lennox has taken a room here.

08:05.760 --> 08:08.200
They sail on
this evening's tide.

08:08.200 --> 08:11.760
-You came.
-Gave my word.

08:11.760 --> 08:13.240
-Thank you.
-Come on.

08:19.840 --> 08:23.880
Are you not delighted
with your witness?

08:23.880 --> 08:27.320
(Quigley chuckles)

08:27.320 --> 08:28.680
I sent her to you.

08:28.680 --> 08:33.080
I have found your murderer.

08:33.080 --> 08:35.720
Now you have no excuse.

08:35.720 --> 08:37.960
Release Charlotte Wells.

08:37.960 --> 08:40.200
I'm already signing her papers.

08:42.280 --> 08:44.600
(Quigley laughs)

08:44.600 --> 08:46.080
How is your son?

08:46.080 --> 08:49.320
Fit and well.

08:49.320 --> 08:51.800
Emily Lacey will not
trouble him again.

08:56.320 --> 08:59.080
Were the Spartans not satisfied?

08:59.080 --> 09:00.680
Satisfied and sated.

09:00.680 --> 09:02.040
The venture's at an end.

09:02.040 --> 09:04.560
Your services are
required no more.

09:04.560 --> 09:09.160
Now leave this court or you'll
find my justice ruthless.

09:09.160 --> 09:19.320
♪

09:19.320 --> 09:20.840
Take Jacob upstairs.

09:20.840 --> 09:22.080
♪

09:22.080 --> 09:23.560
I'll distract him.

09:23.560 --> 09:26.840
♪

09:26.840 --> 09:29.080
Mr. Lennox.

09:29.080 --> 09:31.480
I've come to ask you
one last time.

09:31.480 --> 09:33.480
Give Harriet's children up.

09:33.480 --> 09:36.440
They're mine to sell
or keep as I please.

09:36.440 --> 09:38.680
♪

09:38.680 --> 09:40.440
What would my value be?

09:40.440 --> 09:42.320
I'm numerate, reliable,

09:42.320 --> 09:44.320
good in a fight.

09:44.320 --> 09:45.920
What would you pay?

09:45.920 --> 09:47.920
Fifteen pounds
for an uppity old fool.

09:47.920 --> 09:50.080
In the same marketplace,
what would I pay for you?

09:50.080 --> 09:51.440
♪

09:51.440 --> 09:53.680
Because as far as I can see,
you've not one quality

09:53.680 --> 09:57.440
of strength or character
that makes you worth tuppence.

09:57.440 --> 10:00.320
What trouble that
whore has put you up to

10:00.320 --> 10:02.360
for two tiresome brats.

10:02.360 --> 10:05.200
Now step aside.

10:05.200 --> 10:07.560
My boat sails
and I want a drink.

10:07.560 --> 10:09.840
I've spent my whole life

10:09.840 --> 10:11.840
lowering my eyes
to men like you,

10:11.840 --> 10:14.680
turning my back,
saving my skin.

10:14.680 --> 10:19.360
This time, I'll not
turn away nor step aside.

10:19.360 --> 10:21.680
♪

10:21.680 --> 10:23.080
You can go to hell.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.560
♪

10:25.560 --> 10:26.920
See you there.

10:26.920 --> 10:29.840
♪

10:29.840 --> 10:32.720
Thief!

10:32.720 --> 10:34.320
Call the watch.

10:34.320 --> 10:35.440
Bring the constable.

10:35.440 --> 10:36.920
This man is a thief.

10:36.920 --> 10:40.200
This villain would
steal these children

10:40.200 --> 10:41.480
from their mother.

10:41.480 --> 10:44.160
They're my property!

10:44.160 --> 10:45.960
I say we take the
matter before a judge

10:45.960 --> 10:47.320
and let the law decide.

10:47.320 --> 10:50.320
I have all the documents
to prove those brats are mine.

10:50.320 --> 10:52.560
They are mine
by the laws of God.

10:52.560 --> 10:54.200
Take us to the magistrate.

10:54.200 --> 10:55.560
We let the law decide.

10:55.560 --> 10:56.960
We will settle this now.

10:56.960 --> 10:59.920
Will it be murder then,
Mr. Lennox?

10:59.920 --> 11:01.720
Because you will have
to kill us both!

11:01.720 --> 11:13.200
♪

11:13.200 --> 11:16.960
You can keep the half-breeds
and God damn you.

11:16.960 --> 11:19.480
-He's the criminal!
-Disgusting!

11:24.040 --> 11:27.680
Miss Wells,
you are free to go.

11:27.680 --> 11:29.720
I knew the lies
would not stand up.

11:29.720 --> 11:31.840
Not you.

11:31.840 --> 11:33.840
You stay.

11:33.840 --> 11:35.200
He's innocent.

11:35.200 --> 11:36.720
If I'm free then so is he.

11:36.720 --> 11:39.440
Charlotte, go.

11:39.440 --> 11:40.960
Take your freedom.

11:43.160 --> 11:46.720
I'll get you out
before the day is done.

11:46.720 --> 11:48.360
Trust me.

12:07.280 --> 12:08.600
(tapping on glass)

12:10.200 --> 12:11.600
Miss Wells.

12:11.600 --> 12:13.080
Miss Wells, a word!

12:13.080 --> 12:14.160
Leave me alone.

12:14.160 --> 12:17.560
No, I've been
contriving your release

12:17.560 --> 12:19.080
ever since I heard
of your arrest.

12:19.080 --> 12:20.920
-Nonsense.
-I've been petitioning for you.

12:20.920 --> 12:22.440
To hang?

12:22.440 --> 12:24.160
You'd enjoy anything
that gave my mother pain.

12:24.160 --> 12:25.440
No, please, please!

12:25.440 --> 12:27.680
Believe me, I am your friend.

12:30.040 --> 12:32.080
No one else
is here to help you.

12:35.560 --> 12:36.960
Please let me
offer you at least,

12:36.960 --> 12:40.840
at the very least,
a meal and a resting place.

12:40.840 --> 12:43.040
There's an innocent
man in there.

12:43.040 --> 12:45.560
I don't need a rest.

12:45.560 --> 12:46.840
I need to get him out.

12:46.840 --> 12:48.080
Oh, my dear.

12:49.680 --> 12:52.320
Justice Cunliffe
is an intimate of mine.

12:52.320 --> 12:54.480
I have his ear,
as you can see.

12:56.040 --> 12:57.360
Come with me.

12:59.200 --> 13:02.680
And we will very soon
devise your friend's release.

13:07.560 --> 13:08.960
Ah, yes.

13:12.560 --> 13:20.160
♪

13:20.160 --> 13:21.800
Charlotte!

13:21.800 --> 13:23.160
Charlotte!

13:23.160 --> 13:24.360
Charlotte!

13:24.360 --> 13:25.560
♪

13:25.560 --> 13:26.920
Charlotte!

13:26.920 --> 13:28.800
♪

13:28.800 --> 13:30.080
Charlotte!

13:30.080 --> 13:40.600
♪

13:45.560 --> 13:52.160
♪

13:52.160 --> 13:53.560
Welcome, my dear.

13:53.560 --> 13:57.680
♪

13:57.680 --> 13:59.040
(Quigley clears her throat)

13:59.040 --> 14:00.680
♪

14:00.680 --> 14:04.800
May I introduce
Miss Charlotte Wells.

14:04.800 --> 14:07.680
She walked free from
the courthouse this morning,

14:07.680 --> 14:11.040
victim of a false accusation.

14:11.040 --> 14:13.360
Prepare a room
and a choice of gowns.

14:13.360 --> 14:14.840
Why have you brought her here?

14:14.840 --> 14:16.960
I'm offering her charity.

14:16.960 --> 14:19.280
(chatter)

14:22.680 --> 14:24.320
Justice.

14:24.320 --> 14:27.600
The bawd, Lydia Quigley.

14:27.600 --> 14:29.280
Why have you not acted
when you've heard

14:29.280 --> 14:31.080
a charge of
kidnapping against her?

14:32.800 --> 14:34.920
Has the unfortunate Mr. Oswald

14:34.920 --> 14:36.560
been speaking to you?

14:36.560 --> 14:38.280
Yes.

14:38.280 --> 14:41.320
That young man
is such a disappointment.

14:43.840 --> 14:47.680
He constantly debauches
himself with harlots.

14:47.680 --> 14:49.320
I've warned him several times

14:49.320 --> 14:52.280
and he knows his position
is in the balance.

14:52.280 --> 14:54.560
I suspect he seeks
to save himself

14:54.560 --> 14:56.440
by sullying my name.

14:57.920 --> 14:59.280
I see.

14:59.280 --> 15:00.920
I looked into this kidnap;

15:00.920 --> 15:03.440
a tawdry dispute
between whores.

15:04.960 --> 15:06.920
Corruption is a cancer.

15:06.920 --> 15:10.560
And to see it take root
in a man like that.

15:10.560 --> 15:12.920
We must be vigilant
against it, John.

15:12.920 --> 15:15.840
Justice is a wellspring.

15:15.840 --> 15:18.200
The whole city suffers

15:18.200 --> 15:20.320
when it's poisoned
near the head.

15:32.200 --> 15:33.480
You fool.

15:33.480 --> 15:35.160
You have besmirched yourself.

15:35.160 --> 15:37.200
How can I act upon
the word of a degenerate?

15:37.200 --> 15:39.360
Sir, I'm telling the truth.

15:41.080 --> 15:43.720
When I return,
you will be gone for good.

15:43.720 --> 15:47.440
At liberty to fuck yourself
into an early grave.

15:48.960 --> 15:53.160
I'm here because you said
you'd speak for Mr. Marney.

15:53.160 --> 15:56.440
There's a spark in you.

15:56.440 --> 15:59.320
You were born under my roof
and I saw it from the start.

15:59.320 --> 16:01.320
I tried to draw it out.

16:01.320 --> 16:03.480
Something quite exceptional.

16:03.480 --> 16:05.480
My mother told me you were
clever with your praise.

16:05.480 --> 16:07.680
I want you in my house.

16:07.680 --> 16:08.960
When will you see the justice?

16:08.960 --> 16:10.320
Directly.

16:12.200 --> 16:14.200
Stay.

16:14.200 --> 16:17.560
Lick your wounds,
be the phoenix, rise.

16:17.560 --> 16:19.440
So you may lock me in

16:19.440 --> 16:21.320
like the pallid
China dolls out there?

16:21.320 --> 16:24.560
You need another keeper
and you'll find one here.

16:24.560 --> 16:27.320
You will have every freedom
and you'll keep all you earn,

16:27.320 --> 16:31.200
and believe me, I have never
offered terms like that.

16:33.800 --> 16:36.360
Why do it now?

16:36.360 --> 16:37.680
What do you gain?

16:39.480 --> 16:42.080
You saw their faces
when I brought you here.

16:45.680 --> 16:47.160
I gain you.

16:48.680 --> 16:51.200
Your notoriety.

16:51.200 --> 16:53.680
Your company.

16:53.680 --> 16:54.720
Charlotte Wells!

16:56.200 --> 16:57.840
Charlotte Wells!

16:59.680 --> 17:00.920
Charlotte!

17:00.920 --> 17:03.200
What possesses you to
come here with this witch?

17:03.200 --> 17:05.600
She'll lock the doors
and keep you here by force!

17:08.080 --> 17:09.240
Let her in.

17:10.480 --> 17:12.000
Gentlemen,

17:12.000 --> 17:14.280
let's take our
pleasure upstairs.

17:18.760 --> 17:21.320
What are you doing here?

17:21.320 --> 17:23.040
I had nowhere else to go.

17:23.040 --> 17:24.080
Come home.

17:24.080 --> 17:25.400
Where's that?

17:25.400 --> 17:27.480
With me.

17:27.480 --> 17:29.240
I asked you twice
to take me in

17:29.240 --> 17:31.080
and you refused.

17:31.080 --> 17:32.640
Come now.

17:32.640 --> 17:34.560
How can you let her
dupe and beguile you?

17:34.560 --> 17:36.840
Mrs. Quigley got me out of jail.

17:38.560 --> 17:40.760
You let them arrest me, Ma.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.560
And Daniel Marney too.

17:44.000 --> 17:45.000
I did not.

17:45.000 --> 17:47.040
You sent the
constables to take him.

17:47.040 --> 17:48.560
That's a lie.

17:48.560 --> 17:50.120
I did everything
I could to get you out!

17:50.120 --> 17:51.840
Such as?

17:51.840 --> 18:01.320
♪

18:01.320 --> 18:03.800
Tell me...

18:03.800 --> 18:05.360
where is Emily Lacey?

18:05.360 --> 18:06.840
♪

18:06.840 --> 18:10.560
-I have no idea.
-Did you kill her yet?

18:10.560 --> 18:13.120
Or is she still locked
and beaten in your crypt?

18:13.120 --> 18:14.640
♪

18:14.640 --> 18:17.560
If you thought Miss Lacey
was in danger...

18:17.560 --> 18:19.800
♪

18:19.800 --> 18:21.840
...why did you tell me
where to find her?

18:21.840 --> 18:25.040
♪

18:25.040 --> 18:27.640
(knocking at door)

18:31.840 --> 18:35.320
Ah, hello, grunt.

18:35.320 --> 18:37.320
Where's the she-wolf?

18:39.880 --> 18:41.120
I'm going to get
the law on you

18:41.120 --> 18:42.880
for kidnapping Emily Lacey.

18:42.880 --> 18:44.560
The law will get you first

18:44.560 --> 18:47.160
for the murder
of George Howard.

18:51.480 --> 18:55.000
Oh, this is wonderful.

18:55.000 --> 18:57.120
My two favorite ladies.

18:58.480 --> 19:00.560
What's the matter, Mrs. Q?

19:00.560 --> 19:03.280
Is it the powder
or have you seen a ghost?

19:05.720 --> 19:08.480
What crime were you
planning to accuse me of?

19:08.480 --> 19:10.320
Miss Lacey, perhaps
you'd care to take some tea--

19:10.320 --> 19:12.120
I've come to take
a lot more than that.

19:12.120 --> 19:13.800
You threw me to her
like a piece of scrag

19:13.800 --> 19:16.160
and you will answer for it.

19:24.600 --> 19:26.120
She knows.

19:27.560 --> 19:30.320
What did you tell her?

19:30.320 --> 19:31.360
Nothing.

19:33.600 --> 19:34.840
She knows.

19:34.840 --> 19:37.480
Straightaway you conclude
that I betrayed you?

19:37.480 --> 19:39.120
You're betraying me
by being here.

19:39.120 --> 19:41.560
She offered me her help.

19:41.560 --> 19:43.800
If you believe that,
you're an idiot.

19:43.800 --> 19:45.800
I'm an idiot no longer.

19:45.800 --> 19:48.080
I've heeded the lesson
that you taught me.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.720
The only safety is in money.

19:52.720 --> 19:55.480
Money is a woman's
only power in this world.

19:57.160 --> 19:58.640
I'll earn mine here.

20:00.120 --> 20:02.160
She's using you, my love.

20:02.160 --> 20:04.320
As did you.

20:04.320 --> 20:06.320
Charlotte, come home.

20:06.320 --> 20:09.480
You save Lucy and
abandon me to hang?

20:13.560 --> 20:15.560
♪

20:15.560 --> 20:17.080
I want you to go.

20:17.080 --> 20:42.000
♪

20:45.560 --> 20:46.720
Oh.

20:48.600 --> 20:51.080
Nancy Birch wants me to squeak.

20:51.080 --> 20:53.160
She says my evidence
would hang you.

20:55.080 --> 20:56.560
I'm willing to stay silent.

20:56.560 --> 20:58.720
I think your death
would upset Charles.

20:58.720 --> 21:00.560
Your story will be
pitched into a midden

21:00.560 --> 21:03.120
and you along with it like
the dung worm that you are.

21:03.120 --> 21:04.840
Don't speak to her like that.

21:07.280 --> 21:09.480
You take her side?

21:09.480 --> 21:11.720
When she threatens
me with hanging?

21:13.760 --> 21:16.560
I followed you to
that infernal house.

21:16.560 --> 21:19.560
I met Justice Cunliffe
and I fobbed him off.

21:19.560 --> 21:23.080
I know what you intended
and it was worse than hanging.

21:25.120 --> 21:26.800
I want recompense.

21:26.800 --> 21:28.840
You shall have it.

21:28.840 --> 21:30.840
Let's start with the deeds

21:30.840 --> 21:32.480
to one of your houses.

21:32.480 --> 21:35.600
I'd like my dresses too.

21:35.600 --> 21:37.480
And a hundred pounds,

21:37.480 --> 21:39.360
just to help me settle in.

21:43.520 --> 21:47.400
Have you forgotten that
she nearly caused your death?

21:47.400 --> 21:50.120
I have forgiven her.

21:50.120 --> 21:51.280
But not you.

21:51.280 --> 21:52.600
I'm your mother!

21:52.600 --> 21:54.480
You're a monster.

21:54.480 --> 21:56.800
Whatever you're involved in,
I want no part of it.

21:58.800 --> 22:00.400
I'm leaving you.

22:00.400 --> 22:03.000
As of this moment,
you're alone.

22:05.280 --> 22:07.120
You've endangered everything.

22:07.120 --> 22:09.520
Miss Lacey will have
all she wants.

22:12.560 --> 22:25.560
♪

22:25.560 --> 22:27.560
Are you going to
help Mr. Marney?

22:27.560 --> 22:28.640
♪

22:28.640 --> 22:31.320
Mr. Abbadon, my coach!

22:31.320 --> 22:32.640
Yes, my lady!

22:32.640 --> 22:35.480
♪

22:35.480 --> 22:36.280
(door slams shut)

22:36.280 --> 22:38.880
♪

22:49.840 --> 22:52.120
Why didn't you tell me
what had happened?

22:52.120 --> 22:54.280
For God's sake,
the girl is still alive

22:54.280 --> 22:57.080
and there is a noose
'round both our necks!

22:57.080 --> 23:00.320
Let me eat in peace
or I will have you removed

23:00.320 --> 23:03.360
as a parasite.

23:03.360 --> 23:07.280
Some parasites bring
ruin on their hosts.

23:11.160 --> 23:13.040
(crowd chatter)

23:15.240 --> 23:16.760
Ma told me to burn it.

23:19.280 --> 23:21.320
Why haven't you?

23:21.320 --> 23:23.120
What if Pa and Jacob
don't come back?

23:23.120 --> 23:25.360
She'll need me
to look after her.

23:27.640 --> 23:30.040
Well, lick my split,
it's Lucy Wells.

23:30.040 --> 23:31.400
-Lay off her.
-Why don't you slink

23:31.400 --> 23:33.120
back home to your slippery ma?

23:33.120 --> 23:36.040
You do something useful.

23:36.040 --> 23:37.640
Take her for a drink.

23:39.600 --> 23:41.560
Lucy.

23:41.560 --> 23:44.040
The sky will not fall down.

23:47.080 --> 23:50.880
(children yelling, giggling)

23:50.880 --> 23:53.320
Mrs. Wells and I
parted in discord.

23:54.720 --> 23:56.840
I took her money.

23:56.840 --> 23:58.600
I don't think
she'll want me back.

23:59.880 --> 24:01.560
Leave it to me.

24:03.520 --> 24:06.840
My path was one of anguish.

24:06.840 --> 24:09.040
Now the clouds have cleared.

24:10.800 --> 24:12.240
I don't know how to thank you.

24:12.240 --> 24:14.760
♪

24:14.760 --> 24:15.800
Ma!

24:15.800 --> 24:28.040
♪

24:28.040 --> 24:30.320
(footsteps approaching)

24:41.480 --> 24:44.320
From Harriet.

24:44.320 --> 24:46.240
With her apology.

24:48.400 --> 24:49.760
She should stay.

24:52.400 --> 24:54.080
You took my son.

24:54.080 --> 24:55.400
I'm back.

24:57.320 --> 24:59.840
You left me when
I most needed you.

25:02.560 --> 25:05.240
Cast your mind back
to what I did for you.

25:07.360 --> 25:09.520
When a man has dumped a corpse

25:09.520 --> 25:12.560
he must expiate his sins.

25:14.560 --> 25:18.080
I'd given her my word
and it was right.

25:27.240 --> 25:28.880
Pious cant.

25:30.520 --> 25:33.320
It's clear why you did it.

25:33.320 --> 25:36.080
Go claim your reward.

25:36.080 --> 25:38.280
Is that really what
you think of me?

25:40.800 --> 25:42.880
(knocking at door)

25:45.560 --> 25:48.280
♪

25:48.280 --> 25:49.720
(knocking continues)

25:49.720 --> 25:57.640
♪

25:57.640 --> 25:59.080
Mr. Armitage.

25:59.080 --> 26:02.400
Come for Mrs. Wells,
I must take her to the court.

26:02.400 --> 26:03.800
Why?

26:03.800 --> 26:06.400
The Justice wants to quiz
you, that is all I know.

26:06.400 --> 26:08.240
♪

26:08.240 --> 26:10.320
Whatever for?

26:10.320 --> 26:11.640
That's for him to say.

26:11.640 --> 26:14.120
♪

26:14.120 --> 26:17.280
Amelia Scanwell, a girl
of faultless virtue,

26:17.280 --> 26:19.480
told me she saw
Sir George Howard

26:19.480 --> 26:21.480
carried lifeless
from your house.

26:21.480 --> 26:23.400
The Scanwell girl is lying,

26:23.400 --> 26:25.000
and I'll tell her so in court.

26:25.000 --> 26:27.320
You put his carcass into a coach

26:27.320 --> 26:30.360
and dumped it into
St. James's Pond.

26:30.360 --> 26:32.480
How did he die?

26:32.480 --> 26:34.400
Did you do it yourself,

26:34.400 --> 26:36.520
or are you protecting someone?

26:36.520 --> 26:37.520
No, sir.

26:37.520 --> 26:39.040
Your blackamoor?

26:39.040 --> 26:40.320
He's a good man.

26:40.320 --> 26:42.320
One of your whores?

26:42.320 --> 26:44.400
My girls have done
nothing wrong.

26:44.400 --> 26:47.160
And neither have I.

26:47.160 --> 26:49.120
Perhaps your daughter objected

26:49.120 --> 26:51.520
to her older sister's castoff.

26:51.520 --> 26:53.920
She was happy
for such a keeper.

26:53.920 --> 26:55.520
She was glad.

26:55.520 --> 26:58.240
♪

26:58.240 --> 27:00.480
I'd like to hear her
tell me so herself.

27:00.480 --> 27:01.640
No.

27:01.640 --> 27:03.640
♪

27:03.640 --> 27:05.240
She's just a child.

27:05.240 --> 27:07.560
A child with such a mother.

27:07.560 --> 27:12.120
And what will become
of her when you burn?

27:12.120 --> 27:13.600
You did it,

27:13.600 --> 27:16.320
or your daughter did.

27:16.320 --> 27:19.280
And you'll take the noose
to protect her--I admire that,

27:19.280 --> 27:23.080
I admire your fortitude,
Margaret Wells.

27:23.080 --> 27:25.080
-I'll bring her before me.
-Please.

27:25.080 --> 27:28.240
♪

27:28.240 --> 27:30.600
I beg you; not Lucy.

27:30.600 --> 27:34.120
♪

27:34.120 --> 27:35.720
Get what you want from me.

27:35.720 --> 27:39.800
♪

27:39.800 --> 27:41.840
What if you could walk away,

27:41.840 --> 27:46.120
go back home and
carry on your trade?

27:46.120 --> 27:50.000
No one knows the virgin's
accusation but myself.

27:50.000 --> 27:55.840
♪

27:55.840 --> 28:01.040
What I want is a maiden,
chaste and pure.

28:01.040 --> 28:02.560
♪

28:02.560 --> 28:04.920
Bring me the Scanwell girl

28:04.920 --> 28:09.160
and this charge
will be snuffed out.

28:09.160 --> 28:11.720
I'm not that kind of bawd.

28:11.720 --> 28:14.080
You will be,

28:14.080 --> 28:16.520
or your scruples can console you

28:16.520 --> 28:20.760
when you're twitching
in the noose.

28:20.760 --> 28:24.320
I have a house
in Denmark Street.

28:24.320 --> 28:49.760
♪

28:56.080 --> 28:57.760
-Well done, sir.
-Thank you, gentlemen.

28:57.760 --> 29:01.120
-Thank you very much.
-He won nearly every hand.

29:01.120 --> 29:03.760
Lord Fallon.

29:03.760 --> 29:06.360
Go away, bawd, I don't want you.

29:12.640 --> 29:15.000
I have come to give warning.

29:18.280 --> 29:23.320
Justice Cunliffe is
planning to betray you.

29:23.320 --> 29:26.560
And the next time
he says he has a girl,

29:26.560 --> 29:30.120
it is a snare.

29:30.120 --> 29:34.120
I have no idea what
your prattle means.

29:34.120 --> 29:38.120
Some men are not fit
to serve the Spartans.

29:38.120 --> 29:40.320
He seeks to bring you down.

29:43.600 --> 29:45.920
Will you play, Madam Quigley?

29:51.920 --> 29:57.360
The game you are engaged
in has great risk.

29:57.360 --> 30:02.320
I am the finest
player in the field.

30:02.320 --> 30:06.080
I find a girl and
I leave no trace.

30:08.920 --> 30:12.320
For the Spartans to
endure their pursuits,

30:12.320 --> 30:15.080
they would do well
to come to me.

30:15.080 --> 30:17.560
You don't need
a spineless go-between

30:17.560 --> 30:20.600
whose master is the law.

30:20.600 --> 30:23.400
You need a high priestess.

30:39.880 --> 30:41.400
(knocking)

30:45.920 --> 30:47.360
I implore you,

30:47.360 --> 30:51.160
go to the courthouse
and take back your lies.

30:51.160 --> 30:54.040
Have you come to
his funeral supper?

30:56.280 --> 30:59.080
How dare you set
foot in my house?

30:59.080 --> 31:01.520
I have no right to ask
anything from you,

31:01.520 --> 31:03.760
but an innocent man
is going to die.

31:03.760 --> 31:05.280
Another of your lovers.

31:07.360 --> 31:09.600
His trial is tomorrow.

31:09.600 --> 31:12.040
Mr. Haxby's lies condemn him.

31:13.800 --> 31:15.560
On the night your husband died,

31:15.560 --> 31:17.280
he declared that we
were bruised and bloody

31:17.280 --> 31:18.640
from a fight--not true.

31:18.640 --> 31:22.640
You were drunk on
violence and murder.

31:22.640 --> 31:24.280
Mr. Haxby is an upright man.

31:24.280 --> 31:26.760
Why would he tell
such vicious lies?

31:26.760 --> 31:29.600
Because some men feel
their lust as hate.

31:31.840 --> 31:33.080
Tell me.

31:34.880 --> 31:37.840
Did you pin it to the harlot?

31:37.840 --> 31:40.480
You wanted her brought low.

31:40.480 --> 31:43.360
You practically bid it.

31:43.360 --> 31:46.800
I embellished the facts
not to fabricate her guilt

31:46.800 --> 31:49.040
but to enhance it.

31:50.840 --> 31:55.080
-I dismiss you from my service.
-My lady...

31:55.080 --> 31:58.000
Your judgment is
marred with grief.

31:58.000 --> 32:00.320
-Accept my guidance--
-I am a widow,

32:00.320 --> 32:03.320
and I suffer no
man's guidance now.

32:03.320 --> 32:05.080
In full command of my wits,

32:05.080 --> 32:07.880
I say take your things and go.

32:19.320 --> 32:23.640
This...harlot caused
my master's death.

32:23.640 --> 32:25.920
That is the abiding truth.

32:28.520 --> 32:32.000
(guests murmuring)

32:35.080 --> 32:38.880
Who killed my husband?

32:38.880 --> 32:40.800
Villains, perhaps?

32:40.800 --> 32:43.320
Like they say.

32:43.320 --> 32:46.080
Whoever they are,

32:46.080 --> 32:47.520
I am free.

32:51.560 --> 32:53.640
I'll speak for your friend.

32:56.840 --> 33:00.120
Christ forgave
Mary Magdalene for her sins.

33:00.120 --> 33:02.000
That's a new tune,
Mrs. Scanwell.

33:02.000 --> 33:04.560
Mrs. Wells.

33:04.560 --> 33:05.840
How do you fare?

33:05.840 --> 33:08.480
Very well.

33:08.480 --> 33:11.000
My Charlotte's been released.

33:11.000 --> 33:12.240
The matter's at an end.

33:12.240 --> 33:14.840
I am profoundly glad to hear it.

33:16.640 --> 33:19.760
Do you still wish to
leave Mrs. Quigley's pay?

33:19.760 --> 33:23.080
It is a blight
on both our lives.

33:23.080 --> 33:26.120
I know of a house

33:26.120 --> 33:28.320
that you could take for a while.

33:28.320 --> 33:30.560
I offer it as
charity, of course.

33:30.560 --> 33:32.600
Perhaps your daughter would

33:32.600 --> 33:36.560
like to see the place to
see if it is convenient.

33:36.560 --> 33:40.000
Mrs. Wells, you are too good.

33:40.000 --> 33:54.400
♪

34:03.080 --> 34:08.160
Mrs. Quigley drained my mother
of her strength and health.

34:08.160 --> 34:10.000
But she's recovering.

34:11.720 --> 34:13.000
Here.

34:20.200 --> 34:25.320
♪

34:25.320 --> 34:27.800
We want to start
a house of penitence,

34:27.800 --> 34:33.280
a place where fallen girls
may come to find God's love.

34:33.280 --> 34:35.960
This house would mark
a new beginning.

34:35.960 --> 34:54.040
♪

34:54.040 --> 34:57.280
I did you wrong, Mrs. Wells.

34:57.280 --> 35:00.280
I went to the
courthouse this morning.

35:00.280 --> 35:02.400
I meant you no ill will.

35:02.400 --> 35:04.320
I was forced.

35:04.320 --> 35:07.840
♪

35:07.840 --> 35:09.840
Don't drink it.

35:15.320 --> 35:18.880
In return for my life,

35:18.880 --> 35:21.440
Justice Cunliffe told
me to bring you here.

35:21.440 --> 35:23.280
What does he intend?

35:23.280 --> 35:26.000
A coach will come for you.

35:26.000 --> 35:28.760
You will not return.

35:28.760 --> 35:41.520
♪

35:41.520 --> 35:42.840
Come here.

35:42.840 --> 35:46.720
♪

35:46.720 --> 35:48.400
Who you spying for?

35:48.400 --> 35:51.720
I'm watching over my
friend, Miss Scanwell.

35:51.720 --> 35:53.960
She's in grave danger.

35:53.960 --> 35:56.720
I need you to fetch
Nancy Birch and Mr. North.

35:56.720 --> 35:58.000
Help us.

35:58.000 --> 36:06.800
♪

36:06.800 --> 36:08.800
You need to go home.

36:10.640 --> 36:13.520
To catch a beast,

36:13.520 --> 36:15.840
you must have bait.

36:15.840 --> 36:20.280
♪

36:20.280 --> 36:23.760
(noisy kissing)

36:25.800 --> 36:27.600
Does she like him?

36:27.600 --> 36:29.520
Or will she charge him for that?

36:29.520 --> 36:31.040
Yes and yes.

36:35.680 --> 36:37.800
I hate culls.

36:41.920 --> 36:43.880
I need you.

36:49.640 --> 36:51.520
Master yourself!

36:59.360 --> 37:03.240
♪

37:03.240 --> 37:04.920
(knocking at door)

37:04.920 --> 37:25.320
♪

37:25.320 --> 37:27.480
Nancy's going for the law.

37:27.480 --> 37:36.880
♪

37:36.880 --> 37:39.200
(carriage trundling)

37:39.200 --> 37:49.200
♪

37:49.200 --> 37:50.800
(door slams shut)

37:50.800 --> 38:00.320
♪

38:00.320 --> 38:02.440
You've done well.

38:02.440 --> 38:04.240
It was easier than I thought.

38:04.240 --> 38:06.200
Once your conscience peels away,

38:06.200 --> 38:08.120
you'll find you can do anything.

38:08.120 --> 38:10.440
You'd like to rise,
wouldn't you?

38:10.440 --> 38:12.640
Like Lydia Quigley.

38:12.640 --> 38:14.960
She's had my protection
this last 20 years,

38:14.960 --> 38:16.640
but her day is done.

38:16.640 --> 38:21.400
Her fall marks your ascent.

38:21.400 --> 38:24.880
No doubt you'll thrive
as well as she.

38:24.880 --> 38:25.880
Come on.

38:25.880 --> 38:33.200
♪

38:33.200 --> 38:36.160
Suffering purifies the soul.

38:36.160 --> 38:40.520
It will bring you closer to God.

38:40.520 --> 38:43.840
-Cunliffe, Justice Cunliffe!
-This is kidnap!

38:43.840 --> 38:45.920
(shouting, clamor)

38:45.920 --> 38:47.600
Just go!

38:47.600 --> 38:48.800
(stabbing)

38:48.800 --> 38:58.800
♪

38:58.800 --> 39:00.160
He's injured.

39:00.160 --> 39:01.200
There's blood.

39:01.200 --> 39:02.200
He's--he's hit.

39:02.200 --> 39:03.360
He's been stabbed!

39:03.360 --> 39:06.640
♪

39:06.640 --> 39:09.640
(labored groan)

39:09.640 --> 39:23.400
♪

39:23.400 --> 39:24.800
(clattering clank)

39:24.800 --> 39:33.920
♪

39:33.920 --> 39:35.320
A thousand thanks,
Lady Caroline,

39:35.320 --> 39:36.640
for the service you've done me.

39:36.640 --> 39:38.840
A small service.

39:42.920 --> 39:44.520
No one has ever done more.

39:44.520 --> 39:50.640
♪

39:50.640 --> 39:51.920
On you go.

39:51.920 --> 40:05.160
♪

40:12.760 --> 40:14.040
What ails you?

40:16.400 --> 40:18.960
An old friend has died.

40:18.960 --> 40:20.720
Sad news.

40:23.400 --> 40:25.200
My condolences.

40:57.480 --> 40:59.400
What would you say to them all?

41:01.920 --> 41:05.440
The ones who hurt you,
cared nothing for your pain?

41:20.120 --> 41:21.720
(Lucy exclaims)

41:24.240 --> 41:26.160
Show them your strength.

41:27.840 --> 41:30.680
I'll pound you

41:30.680 --> 41:33.640
to tripe,

41:33.640 --> 41:36.360
you worthless grunt!

41:36.360 --> 41:41.040
(whipping, exclaiming)

41:45.680 --> 42:05.680
♪

42:05.680 --> 42:08.000
Charlotte, what
are you doing here?

42:08.000 --> 42:10.320
I will join you directly.

42:18.760 --> 42:22.000
You loved me for a night
and it almost cost your life.

42:23.920 --> 42:27.280
That's not because
of how I felt.

42:27.280 --> 42:28.800
Let's go, come on,
come away with me.

42:28.800 --> 42:31.840
I am not to love or be loved.

42:31.840 --> 42:35.000
What kind of demented
thinking is that?

42:37.520 --> 42:39.360
We could have our freedom.

42:42.320 --> 42:44.840
Be who we please.

42:44.840 --> 42:48.200
I know you feel as
steadfastly as me.

42:48.200 --> 42:50.360
I cannot be with you.

42:53.200 --> 42:57.360
Will I carry you out
of this cage on my back?

42:57.360 --> 42:59.440
Everything I am,

42:59.440 --> 43:03.280
everything my sister is,
comes down to this.

43:03.280 --> 43:05.360
My mother was sold, age 10,

43:05.360 --> 43:07.880
to a bawd who put her
to work as a whore,

43:07.880 --> 43:09.880
Lydia Quigley.

43:09.880 --> 43:13.200
That woman has grown rich
on countless ruined lives.

43:15.120 --> 43:18.360
Fate has put me in her house,

43:18.360 --> 43:20.960
and I will bring her down.

43:20.960 --> 43:25.440
♪

43:25.440 --> 43:27.760
That is my purpose now.

43:27.760 --> 44:25.840
♪

44:25.840 --> 44:28.640
(panting, groaning)

44:28.640 --> 44:47.960
♪

44:47.960 --> 44:51.280
(laughter)

44:51.280 --> 44:53.840
(coins clinking)

44:53.840 --> 44:56.240
♪

44:56.240 --> 44:59.200
(woman sings lullaby in French)

44:59.200 --> 45:02.960
♪

45:02.960 --> 45:05.480
Shh.

45:05.480 --> 45:08.680
(baby fusses)

45:08.680 --> 46:00.880
♪

46:00.880 --> 46:02.440
I'm ready, Ma.

